      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Memm ¶  ¶ The Chief Secretary requests the following information from the Director of the Botanic Gardens: ¶  ¶ The number of men employed in the department on work of a scientific kind only, and thei...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.10.22<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">From</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Thomas Ware<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 2950, V70/14221, unit 471, VPRS 3991/P<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">inward</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Trans 18.1.94. To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">See also No 2950, unit 23, p. 111, VPRS 1187, outward registered correspondence</seg>.</p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">Since M replies to this describing, it as Memorandum No 2950 this note must mean that there is a copy in outwards. It would be more sensible to cite that source I think. I suspect that the</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">Memo was returned with 70-10-22a, as it has the same details as that letter, but without a No: "V70/14221, unit 471, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence VA 475 Chief</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria"</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to McCulloch, 22 October 1870<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">is his reply</seg>.</p>
               </note>Memm</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Chief Secretary requests the following information from the Director of the Botanic Gardens:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The number of men employed in the department on work of a scientific kind only, and their pay</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>2. The names of the men inhabiting cottages within the gardens and an account of the work performed by each.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This information the Chief Secretary desires to have on Monday in connection with the Estimates.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">for the Under Secy</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(Sd) Thos. Webb Ware.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">C. S. Office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">22 Octr 1870.</p>
         </div>
